You teased me for needing to touch your face... but you should know:


I don't know the map of your body as a weary traveller continually walking the same road.
But as a lover who fears blindness upon each awakening
Trying to remember each contour, every freckle
In dread of being robbed of the pleasure

I'm sorry I'm not what you want
I'm not sorry about who I am.

Don't try to buy me off
I still won't conform to your close minded ideals

Taking your money would say that I don't believe in what I do
Why would I want to do that?
It's just not true...

The things I love most about myself are the same as what makes me different from you...
Taking them away would bring up old self hate
That's not something I'm willing to face again, especially not for you.
The one who's supposed to be on my side
The one whose shoulder I'm supposed to lean on, this time made me cry.

Hole number 13... and it's beautiful.
First time I've braved a piercing alone in a while... totally changes the experience. Quite exhilarating I must say.

with someone who is not in love with you, you understand my predicament.
Being in love with you, who are not in love with me, you understand my dilemma.
Being in love with your being in love with me, which you are not, you understand

the difficulty. Being in love with your being, you can well imagine how hard it is. Being in love with your being you, no matter you are not your being being in love with me, you can appreciate and pity being in love with you. Being in love

with someone who is not in love, you know all about being in love when being in love is being in love with someone who is not in love being with you, which is being in love, which you know only too well, 
Love, being in love with being in love.

-Marvin Bell

I want to be a cow 
and not my mother's daughter.
I want to be a cow
and not in love with you.
I want to feel free to feel calm.
I want to be a cow who never knows the kind of love you "fall in love with" with;
a queenly cow, with hips as big and sound as a department store,
a cow the farmer milks on bended knee,
who when she dies will feel dawn
bending over her like lawn to wet her lips.

I want to be a cow,
nothing fancy-
a cargo of grass,
a hammock of soupy milk
whose floating and rocking and dribbling's undisturbed
by the echo of hooves to the city;
of crunching boots;
of suspicious-looking trailers parked on verges;
of unscrupulous restaurant owners
who stumble, pink-eyed, from stale beds
into a world of lobsters and warm telephones;
of streamlined Japanese freighters
ironing into the night,
heavy with sweet desire like bowls of jam.

The Tibetans have 85 words for states consciousness.
This dozy cow I want to be has none.
She doesn't speak
She doesn't do housework or worry about her appearance.
She doesn't roam.
Safe in her fleet
of shorn-white-bowl-like friends,
she needs, and loves, and's loved by.
only this-
the farm I want to be a cow on too. 

Don't come looking for me.
Don't come walking out into the bright sunlight looking for me,
black in your gloves and stockings and sleeves and large hat.
Don't call the tractorman.
Don't call the neighbours.
Don't make a special fruit-cake for when I come home:
I'm not coming home.
I'm going to be a cowman's counted cow.
I'm going to be a cow
and you won't know me.

-SELIMA HILL

I havn't used this in forever..
I don't know where this sudden urge to put this shit up came from.
Ok, I have an idea, but I'm still not sure why I went so crazy with it.
Anyway. I'm sorry for wasting such a large portion of your life with so many entries. Feel free to entirely ignore my following posts should you wish. you are in no way obligated to read them just because I felt like sharing.

I don't know if you've ever loved someone

If you have, I hope they loved you back

If they loved you back
i hope they showed you
I hope they told you

I hope they didn't use you
I hope they didn't play with your mind

I hope they were honest and open
about why you were worth their time

If you love someone, it's something
If someone loves you that's something else
If the person you love loves you back, it's everything

If the person loves you back but can't show it, can't admit it
Can't truly love you back...

It's not worth it.

That's why

I hope if you love someone
I hope if someone loves you back

I hope that you will take advantage
Know what love is worth
and never give it up until it's gone.

Ok
But who will it be? 
the one to come along, to be so perfect, so righteous in influence and love
Someone...
Most be right?
I can't be this way forever, can I?
Hating myself
Loving the world - or at least pretending to.
Hating
Everything
Myself included.
I'm probably at the top of the list.
What does it mean when you ware the first person on your own hit list?
What can be done when one is so hopelessly lost in confusion and pain that sadness seems like their life raft?
When solidarity and abuse are the only way out, should I just stay in?

Here I sit
pondering
rolling ideas over and over in my head
like waves on sand
until my dreams turn to glass
then they are dropped
forgotten, shattered
left to be swept away once again by the turbulent waters which created them
only to be re formed
turned over and over until new pieces have been made
destined to meet the fate of those before them
The same old question being posed..
...wondering intently, desperately

what if this is all there is this really all there is? One shot at life, how do you want to live it? Is this how you want to be remembered? <u>What I see</u>: lonely, depressed, self loathing, cheating, lying, never enough, never knowing, always wondering, hating, loving, unforgiven, weakness, hiding, ugly, waiting, wrong, resentful, wanting, wasted.  <u>What you see:</u> Nothing real, because the real me is lost.
MUST CHANGE, ONLY YOU CAN DO IT, ARE YOU STRONG ENOUGH?

Yearning
  Burning
     Wanting
         Pining
           For
             Love
               Passion
                 Company
                    To
		   Hold me
		     Love me
		       Care for me
			Want to
			   Give 
			     Take
			       Not be
				Alone

I year past, retrogressing... progress made, I love yous' exchanged with myself for the first time; long left behind and replaced with years of self loathing... such deeply ingrained a practice, hate can only be replaced by it's enemy for so long. Feelings of worthlessness... no progress, no future undesired.. there's no easy way out.

The pills take the pain away
The pills make it stop
I can play it up all day
Loving life, free of my need
I come home at night
and to avoid the knife,
I tend to pick up the bottle.
But not the kind filled with liquid glory
The kind with the little tabs of heaven
I let my worries melt away with my pain
and sit
I enjoy things - slow to take the time to listen
They help me love, they help me hate, they help me live
One pill makes you hyper
One pill makes you melt
Worlds collide and the effects are apparent
...I'm melting away...
One with the chair
Just trying to figure out how we all got here.

So many things I want to say...
Can't find the words to do them justice.

Think about your direct bodily experience in life.
No one can lie to you about that.
How many hours a day do you spend in front of a television screen? A computer screen? Behind an automobile screen? What are you being screened from? How much of your life comes at you through a screen, vicariously while you sit and watch. Is watching things as exciting as doing things? Do you have enough time to do all the things you want to? Do you even have enough energy to?

Do you think for yourself, independently, or do you take others' word for trust? How often do you find yourself repeating something you heard another say without it having any bearing on your personal experience; your personal truth? How many hours a day do you sleep? how are you affected by standardized time, designed solely to synchronize your movements with those billions of other people? How long do you go without knowing what time it is? Who or what controls YOUR minutes and hours? the minutes and hours that add up to your life.

How do you feel in large crowds of anonymous masses? Do you find yourself blocking your emotional responses to other human beings? Can you put a value on a beautiful day? How many dollars an hour salary does it take to stay inside and sell things or file papers for someone else? What will you get later that will make up for this day of your life? How many days have you given to such things? (years?!?)

Do you have ideas or do ideas have you?

Who prepares your meals? Do you ever eat by yourself? Do you ever eat standing up? How much do you know about what you eat and where it comes from? Do you trust it? Of our many time and labor saving devices, do you find yourself with more time or ironically less than ever? is it even possible to "save" time?

They're buying your happiness from you

Steal it back
How are you affected by being moved around in prescribed paths, in elevators, buses, subways, highways and sidewalks? By moving, living and working in two and three dimensional grids? How are you affected by being organized, immobilized, and scheduled... instead of wandering, roaming freely and spontaneously? How much freedom of movement do you have - freedom to move through space, to move as far as you want, in new and unexplored directions?
How often are you waiting? Waiting in line, waiting in traffic, waiting to eat, waiting for the bus, waiting for the bathroom - learning to punish, ignore and control your spontaneous urges? How do you feel when you suppress your desires, when you delay or deny yourself pleasure?

D you ever need to be around nature? Have water, leaves, foliage, and animals been replaced by your pet, aquarium, and houseplants?

Do videotapes of yourself and your friends fascinate you, as if somehow you are more real in image then in life? Would a movie about your life be interesting? How do you feel about the non-stop barrage of audio, visual, print, billboard, computer, radio, and robotic voices that guide you though a forest of advertisements? What do they want from you?

How often does your happiness come in conjunction with buying something?

Do you feel like without the mainstream stimuli that you will miss something? Will you? Does it make you tired reacting all the time instead of thinking on your own? When was your last true moment of silence... not white noise but pure silence?

have you ever asked yourself these things?
Do you feel violent impulses?
Do you feel inexorable lonely?
Are you really happy?
Do you ever feel like you are going to lose control?

Do you have the energy to create change?


**I don't know who exactly wrote this. I found it in a book of poetry called Revolution on Canvas. They "seized, interpreted, re-organized, and plagiarized with permission and encouragement from "Days of War Nights of Love" " *****

It was in the march of the winter I turned seventeen
That I bought those pills
I thought I would need
And I wrote a letter to my family
Said it's not your fault
And you've been good to me
It's just lately I've been feeling
Like I don't belong
Like the ground's not mine to walk upon
And I've heard that music
Echo through the house
Where my grandmother drank
By herself
And I sat watching a flower
As it was withering
I was embarrassed by its honesty
So I'd prefer to be remembered as a smiling face
Not this fucking wreck
That's taken its place

So please forgive what I have done
No you can't stay mad at the setting sun
Cause we all get tired, I mean eventually
There is nothing left to do but sleep
sometimes i feel like I'm going to wake up and find out my life was a dream and  I'm just being born....

I have learned my lesson with posting things that I write when I am having an angry at myself / stress out fit, however, it was a very strange feeling to actually utilize the privacy setting on my journal, and then publicizing them later. This wasn't something I thought i was ever going to end up taking part in. Odd ******************************* ***************************************** Atmosphere on April 9... *GASP*!

I just wrote pages in my sketchbook. 
It's amazing how that helps.

approaching life the wrong way as usual
only silence crosses my lips when there are novels to be spoken
can't let it out
just keeping it in
don't know what I'm not saying
don't know what I am
thoughts stopped
stuck in my mind
can't release them
can't find the time
can't do this anymore
can't keep it in
I'm going to fucking pop
if I don't let someone in
my heart and mind are locked up tight
with a chain and lock that I don't even have the key to.
you have the pick
could set me free
just get me talking, and in touch with me.
my mind needs to clear
it just won't happen here
I hurt
inside and out
not anyones fault but my own
my problems
my mind
I'm absorbed, they've sucked me up
can't do this forever
can't do it
my words are all I have
my only expression
can't use them.
they won't come out
I'll open up
and this ugly shell will go away
my hardened exterior can fade away
and the pearl inside can be revealed. 
better off alone
can't hurt others
won't matter when my words can't find the time
I want to stand on the edge
toe the line
between seeing another day and eternity
to let it go
to let it out
when it doesn't help
maybe I'll cross the line 
if it does, maybe next time.

don't lie
don't pretend
It's no fun hurting people
especially your friends.


Be careful what you wish for
be careful for what you dream
when even things right in front of you, aren't always what they seem.

Just wanting to go stand on a cliff and scream at the top of my lungs. 

*there's no place like anywhere but here* *there's no place like anywhere but here* *there's no place like anywhere but here*

My skin is kind of sort of brownish pinkish yellowish white.
My eyes are greyish blueish green, but I'm told they look orange in the night.
My hair is reddish blondish brown, but it's silver hen it's wet.
And all the colors I am inside
Have not been invented yet.

She drank from a bottle called DRINK ME
And up she grew so tall,
She ate from a plate called TASTE ME
And down she shrank so small.
And so she changed, while other folks 
Never tried nothin' at all.

-shel silverstein

the best advice my roommate ever gave me:

If you love something, give it away
If it comes back to you, it's yours
If it doesn't, it never was

Drove down the hill and over the bridge
Over the water was contemplating throwing my self in
to let the water carry me away
over the rocks and down to the waves
continued my journey and it started to pour
I exited the car and slammed the door
I looked at the heavens and screamed with my lungs "WHY CAN'T THINGS WORK OUT, CAN'T I JUST HAVE FUN?!"
Then I realized what I had said 
thought to take my own advice "you can't change others, only yourself"
 if they don't like it, don't put your heart on a shelf.
keep it in your chest right where it belongs, live your life long and be strong.
You are a woman, a beautiful girl
Life is not worth wasting by worrying it away
Get out and live
Do what you want
Those who appreciate you, they will stay
The others for all I care can just walk away
Into the abyss
Into the night
As long as I don't have to deal
No longer willing to fight with myself
Especially not about the people I'm surrounded by

running away...
far far away
to lands unseen and territory unknown 
and I won't be returning
don't wait up for me

Turn the lights up bright
and let me see
your body
Turn the lights up bright
and let me see
those forbidden places we keep in the dark
please share yourself with me. 
Turn the lights up bright
 so I can watch you dance 
let me see your slow and sexy moves
Let me see your body and I'll show you mine
No secrets are kept when we're not in the dark
you can tell me if your pleased without words
Leave the lights on bright
and just let me see, let me see

When you don't know what to think
And you don't know how to act..
Don't act on what you think.

If you could only see
how beautiful she really is

Next time I'll go
and never come back.

I like the sound of that.

I hate inconsistent friends who only want me when I can do something for them. I've put up with it for too long...
Now what's going to happen when I'm not there anymore?
If you won't take the time to take a part in my life, why the hell should I take the time to not only take part in yours, but be at your mercy as to when I get to be your friend?
That's bullshit, not friendship.
I know it's hard... oh believe me do I understand.
But you fucked up your own life, threw your opportunities away. 
Don't take it out on me.

Don't like being cornered
Don't like to admit
Don't ask me questions
Don't try to fix it
I won't tell you anyway
Just leave me alone
I've been dealing with it on my own for 7 years, and I'm doing just fine. Still alive, havn't broken down yet.
Forget I even mentioned it
I wish I hadn't
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The clouds came
and the heavens broke
and clarity rained down on me.

Let's run away to the mountains
Where nothing matters but the weather report.
I'll snowboard all day
And teach lessons for pay
To keep a roof over our heads and the heat on.

I don't care what you do
As long as it matters to you
I'll do anything I can to please you
But be happy, or I'm sorry, you can't stay.

When the sun shines bright, and the weather is warm
When the snow has all gone from the hills
I'll be leaving that day
To follow the freeze
To where snow is falling again

You can come if you please
If not look for me
Next winter, at home, in my cabin.

Screw the what ifs...

Cut loose and just say "fuck it!"....

Forget to listen to yourself...

It only hurts if you let it....

Throw insecurities out the window...

Before you can love someone else, you must love yourself...

Listen to your heart....

Fear is a wasted emotion...
I know what I want to be when I grow up..... alive.

too many things going round in my head makes me dizzy can't pick a direction and walk that way always weaving indecisive on one side of the street or the other must focus my brain see life as a straight red line on the ground ..left, right, left, right... remind myself to walk to proceed and move forward ...left, right, left, right... don't forget there are more things to come, the line is not broken Just remember to keep walking and hold your head high You can be happy, and you will make it to where that line eventually stops just don't let others stand in your way remember who the hell you are ...and don't forget. you are wondeful. The world is your oyster (the vegan version of course) take advantage of it... don't let it take advantage of you.

It's 430am.... I just got home from work, and I'm not passing out. I have enough energy to sit here and talk about nothingness on my livejournal. What an odd feeling.  Caffeine does it's job all too well sometimes.
